From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Will Nelson <will.nelson@discordapp.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Inject markdown_inline into block markdown's (inline) nodes

The upstream tree-sitter-markdown repo ships the grammar split into a
block-level package (`tree-sitter-markdown`, vendored here) and a
companion inline-level package (`tree-sitter-markdown-inline`, not
vendored). Bold/italic/inline-code/link-text are nodes in the inline
grammar; the block grammar exposes their text as opaque `(inline)`
nodes.

arborium-rt vendors the inline grammar locally under
`langs/group-willow/markdown-inline/` (outside this submodule) and
registers it under the id `markdown_inline`. This patch wires the two
together by adding the standard nvim-treesitter injection.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 langs/group-willow/markdown/def/queries/injections.scm | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/langs/group-willow/markdown/def/queries/injections.scm b/langs/group-willow/markdown/def/queries/injections.scm
--- a/langs/group-willow/markdown/def/queries/injections.scm
+++ b/langs/group-willow/markdown/def/queries/injections.scm
@@ -11,3 +11,4 @@

 ((plus_metadata) @injection.content (#set! injection.language "toml"))

+((inline) @injection.content (#set! injection.language "markdown_inline"))
